The paper deals with information transmission over a noisy channel, which is a classic problem in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves devising efficient encoding and decoding procedures, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the frequency of error-causing sequences, which is related to signal processing and machine learning (cs.SI). Finally, the paper touches on issues of continuity and relaxation, which are relevant to network architecture and protocols (cs.NI).
